        <h2>Events for 2016</h2>

        <table>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
            <td class="events">
              <h3><a class="anchor" id="top" name="surc"></a>Sunday afternoon Concerts at SURC</h3>
              <p>The next concert in the SURC concert series is a piano recital by the renowned musician, Tau Way, on Sunday 7th February. The concerts start at 3 pm and last around an hour, followed by tea, coffee and cakes which are included in the price of £7 and £3 (under 18).</p>
              <ul>
                <li><b>7th February</b> Tau Wey - a piano recital by the renowned musician</li>
                <li><b>20th March</b> Croydon Symphonic band</li>
                <li><b>19th June</b> A concert of contrasts with trumpet, organ and harp</li>
                <li><b>24th July</b> Surrey Harmony with their lively ladies' barbershop</li>
            </ul>
            <p>For more information contact: <%= mail_to "sanderstead.music@gmail.com" %>, <%= link_to "www.surc.org.uk", "http://www.surc.org.uk" %> or telephone 07563 917777</p>
            </td>
            <td class="events">
              <%= link_to image_tag("small-images/surc.jpg", alt: "SURC logo"), "http://www.surc.org.uk" %>
            </td>
          </tr>




          <tr>
            <td class="events">
              <h3><a class="anchor" id="top" name="marionf"></a>Guided Walk from Riddlesdown, Friday February 26th 10 am</h3>
              <p>(GR 323 605) Come for an exhilarating two hour walk through varied chalk hill habitats. See downland where sheep and catle graze and follow old routeways. Meet in Riddlesdown Common car park at the end of Riddlesdown Road. Volunteer Marion's walks explore local countryside, wildlife and history. Boots are advised as paths may be muddy, and waterproofs in case of rain. Dogs allowed if on leads. Finish at the start point. Walks are free.</p>
            </td>
            <td class="events">
              <h3><%= link_to("Marion's Walks", "/resource/marion.pdf")%></h3>
            </td>
          </tr>

           <tr>
            <td class="events">
              <h3><a class="anchor" id="top" name="marionm"></a>Guided Walk from Kingswood, Friday March 18th 10 am</h3>
              <p>(GR 349 603) How many kinds of holes can we find? Why were hazels coppiced? A gentle two hour amble starting from where Orcherd Road enters King's Wood. (Off Limpsfield Road, Sanderstead, B269, bus route 403) Volunteer Marion's walks explore local countryside, wildlife and history. Boots are advised as paths may be muddy, and waterproofs in case of rain. Dogs allowed if on leads. Finish at the start point. Walks are free.</p>
            </td>
            <td class="events">
              <h3><%= link_to("Marion's Walks", "/resource/marion.pdf")%></h3>
            </td>
          </tr>

          <tr>
            <td class="events">
