              <p>Held in All Saints' Halls. Put this date in your diary. More details nearer the time</p>
            </td>
            <td class="events">
              <h3>SNC</h3>
            </td>
          </tr>

           <tr>
            <td class="events">
              <h3><a class="anchor" id="top" name="mariona"></a>Guided Walk from Hamsey Green, Sunday April 24th 10 am</h3>
              <p>(GR 351 595) Starting from Hamsey Green Pond on Limpsfield Road, this two hour walk follows a lane along the parish boundary and returns through King's Wood. Volunteer Marion's walks explore local countryside, wildlife and history. Boots are advised as paths may be muddy, and waterproofs in case of rain. Dogs allowed if on leads. Finish at the start point. Walks are free.</p>
            </td>
            <td class="events">
              <h3><%= link_to("Marion's Walks", "/resource/marion.pdf")%></h3>
            </td>
          </tr>

          <tr>
            <td class="events">
              <h3><a class="anchor" id="top" name="agm"></a>The Sanderstead Residents' Association AGM, Thursday 28th April 2016</h3>
              <p>The Sanderstead Residents' Association AGM will be held on Thursday 28th April, in All Saints' Church Hall, Onslow Gardens, Sanderstead, CR2 9AB. There will be a presentation by our local Policing Team at 7.15 pm, and the AGM will begin at 8 pm.</p></td>
            <td class="events"><%= link_to image_tag("small-images/residents_logo100.jpg", alt: "SRA logo"), "http://www.sanderstead-residents.co.uk" %></td>
          </tr>

          <tr>
            <td class="events">
              <h3><a class="anchor" id="top" name="mariona2"></a>Guided Walk in King's Wood, Friday 29th April, 10 am</h3>
              <p>(GR 349 603) Enjoy the freshness of new leaves on our native trees above and delicate flowers at our feet. A gentle two hour amble starting from where Orchard Road enters woodland (off Limpsfield Road, Sanderstead, B269). Volunteer Marion's walks explore local countryside, wildlife and history. Boots are advised as paths may be muddy, and waterproofs in case of rain. Dogs allowed if on leads. Finish at the start point. Walks are free.</p>
            </td>
            <td class="events">
              <h3><%= link_to("Marion's Walks", "/resource/marion.pdf")%></h3>
            </td>
          </tr>

          <tr>
            <td class="events">
              <h3><a class="anchor" id="top" name="festival"></a>Sanderstead Festival of Music and Dance, Saturday 18th June 2016</h3>
              <p>A new venture for Sanderstead Community, a music and dance festival will be held on Saturday 18th June, 2-8 pm. Sponsored by our local Councillors and the Residents' Association, it will be held on the Gruffy and in All Saints' Halls. We are already booking some exciting acts, and if you would like to be involved please contact Dennis King tel: 020 8657 2661, <%= mail_to "chairman@sanderstead-residents.co.uk" %></p>
            </td>
            <td class="events"><%= link_to image_tag("small-images/residents_logo100.jpg", alt: "SRA logo"), "http://www.sanderstead-residents.co.uk" %>
            </td>
          </tr>


           <tr>
            <td class="events">
              <h3><a class="anchor" id="top" name="marionj"></a>Guided Walk on Farthing Downs, Saturday 24th June, 10 am</h3>
              <p>(GR 302 572) See what flowers are now flourishing on slopes where scrub has been removed. Some longish slopes on this easy paced two hour walk exploring a spectular chalk valley. Leave fom Farthing Downs car park, one mile south of Coulsdon South station. Volunteer Marion's walks explore local countryside, wildlife and history. Boots are advised as paths may be muddy, and waterproofs in case of rain. Dogs allowed if on leads. Finish at the start point. Walks are free.</p>
            </td>
            <td class="events">
              <h3><%= link_to("Marion's Walks", "/resource/marion.pdf")%></h3>
            </td>
          </tr>

          <tr>
            <td class="events">
              <h3><a class="anchor" id="top" name="marionj2"></a>Guided Walk on Riddlesdown, Friday 1st July, 10 am</h3>
              <p>(GR 323 605) In areas where sheep and cattle have been grazing the number of flower species has multiplied. Enjoy the colours and the insects they attract. This two hour walk leaves from Riddlesdown Common car park at the top end of Riddlesdown Road. Volunteer Marion's walks explore local countryside, wildlife and history. Boots are advised as paths may be muddy, and waterproofs in case of rain. Dogs allowed if on leads. Finish at the start point. Walks are free.</p>
            </td>
            <td class="events">
              <h3><%= link_to("Marion's Walks", "/resource/marion.pdf")%></h3>
            </td>
          </tr>


